This paper deals with the design of a market mechanism for TV white space networks, which involves the allocation of spectrum and the sale of information. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), game theory (cs.GT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given the focus on wireless networks and market design, cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely categories. However, the use of game-theoretic models and security considerations suggest that cs.GT and cs.CR are also relevant. Finally, the potential applications of TV white space networks for multimedia content delivery make cs.MM a plausible category as well.
